  "prompt": "How do I reduce headache?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to reduce headaches:\n\n1. Hydration\n- Drink plenty of water\n- Avoid alcohol and caffeine\n\n2. Rest and relaxation\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Practice stress management techniques\n- Try relaxation methods like deep breathing or meditation\n\n3. Over-the-counter pain relief\n- Take acetaminophen, ibuprofen, or aspirin\n- Follow recommended dosage\n\n4. Environmental adjustments\n- Reduce screen time\n- Minimize bright lights and loud noises\n- Maintain comfortable room temperature\n\n5. Natural remedies\n- Apply cold or hot compress\n- Massage temples and neck\n- Try essential oils like peppermint or lavender\n\n6. Lifestyle modifications\n- Maintain regular sleep schedule\n- Exercise regularly\n- Eat balanced diet\n- Manage stress levels\n\n7. Identify and avoid triggers\n- Certain foods\n- Specific scents\n- Stress\n- Lack of sleep\n\n8. Posture and ergonomics\n- Maintain good posture\n- Use ergonomic workspace setup\n\n9. When persistent or severe, consult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.\n\nRemember, different methods work for different people, so find what works best for you.",
